'''Joannes Theodorus Maria "Jan" Bank''' (born 10 May 1940, [[Amsterdam]])  is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[historian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nwo.nl/nwohome.nsf/pages/NWOP_65YFNU_Eng |title=Dutch culture translated into English |date=21 October 2004 |publisher=Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research |accessdate=25 September 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110920195155/http://www.nwo.nl/nwohome.nsf/pages/NWOP_65YFNU_Eng |archivedate=20 September 2011 |df= }}</ref> He was one of the members of the independent committee assigned responsibility for the fourteenth and final volume of [[Loe de Jong]]'s ''[[The Kingdom of the Netherlands During World War II]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://admin.nrcboeken.nl/recensie/over-het-nut-en-nadeel-van-geschiedschrijving-voor-het-rijk|title=Over het Nut en Nadeel van Geschiedsschrijving voor het Rijk|last=Kristel|first=Connie|date=6 July 1991|work=[[NRC Handelsblad]]|accessdate=12 December 2011}}</ref>

Bank was a member of the [[municipal council (Netherlands)|municipal council]] of [[Amstelveen]] for the [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|Labour Party]] (PvdA).

