{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} The '''Society for Commercial Archeology''' (SCA) is an organization based in [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]]. It is the oldest national organization devoted to the buildings, artifacts, structures, signs, and symbols of the 20th-century commercial landscape.{{citation needed|date=October 2007}} The SCA activities include publications, conferences, and tours to help preserve, document, and celebrate the structures and architecture of the 20th century, including diners, highways, gas stations, drive-in theaters, bus stations, tourist courts, neon signs.
==External links== *[http://www.sca-roadside.org/ Official website]
