{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox UN resolution |number = 524 |organ = SC |date = 29 November |year = 1982 |meeting = 2,403 |code = S/RES/524 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/524(1982) |for = 15 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = Israel-Syrian Arab Republic |result = Adopted |image = Golan Heights Map.PNG |caption = Golan Heights }}
'''United Nations Security Council resolution 524''', adopted unanimously on 29 November 1982, considered a report by the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] regarding the [[United Nations Disengagement Observer Force]]. The Council noted its efforts to establish a durable and just peace in the Middle East but also expressed its concern over the prevailing state of tension in the area.
The resolution decided to call upon the parties concerned to immediately implement [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 338|Resolution 338]] (1973), it renewed the mandate of the Observer Force for another six months until 31 May 1983 and requested that the Secretary-General submit a report on the situation at the end of that period.
